  <h2>Neighborhoods and Areas I Buy In</h2>
  <p><strong>College Hill</strong> — The historic core of Wichita. 1920s-1940s craftsman bungalows, large lots, original details. Foundation issues are common, materials are original and aging. These homes have equity but need serious work.</p>
  <p><strong>Riverside</strong> — Older homes along the Arkansas River, mixed ages, character properties. Good bones, older systems. Popular for restoration, but also where I buy distressed estates.</p>
  <p><strong>East Wichita</strong> — Massive stretch of 1950s-1970s ranch and post-war homes. This is volume territory. Dated systems, roof failures, tenant-trashed rentals. Also where I find inherited properties where heirs don't want the hassle.</p>
  <p><strong>Delano</strong> — West side, mixed age, gentrification happening but still mixed property condition. Industrial-adjacent in some areas. Good opportunities for fast sales.</p>
  <p><strong>Crown Heights and Linwood</strong> — More expensive, better-maintained, but divorce and estate sales still happen here. Higher equity, cleaner transactions.</p>
  <p><strong>West Wichita</strong> — Newer development, better systems, family homes. People buy here to upgrade, then need to sell the old place fast.</p>

